libeasyfc
------------------------------------------
libeasyfc is an interface library to generate fontconfig configuration for
user preferences. this supports to assign your preferrable fonts to the alias
fonts, such as sans-serif, serif and monospace per languages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.6.1-1
  girepository-GLib2.0-1.46.0-1
  girepository-x11-1.46.0-1
  libeasyfc-devel-0.13.1-1bl1
  libeasyfc0-0.13.1-1bl1
  libfontconfig-devel-2.12.1-1
  libfontconfig1-2.12.1-1
  libfreetype6-2.6.5-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.46.2-4
  libglib2.0_0-2.46.2-4
  libharfbuzz0-1.3.3-1
  libxml2-2.9.4-1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.23.0-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  gobject-introspection-1.46.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-4
  make-4.2.1-1
  python-2.7.12-1

Canonical website:
  http://tagoh.bitbucket.org/libeasyfc/

Canonical download:
  https://bitbucket.org/tagoh/libeasyfc/downloads/libeasyfc-0.13.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libeasyfc-0.13.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libeasyfc-0.13.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-0.13.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-0.13.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc0-0.13.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libeasyfc-devel-0.13.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/girepository-Easyfc0.12-0.13.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

